OL,3,CNI's Department of Health preparing
OL,4,Cfor disposable vape ban
OL,6,FDisposable vapes have been pushing the
OL,7,Frise in youth vaping, with the
OL,8,Fproportion of 11 to 17-year-old vapers
OL,9,Fusing disposables increasing almost
OL,10,Fninefold in the last two years, it
OL,11,Fadded.JIn Britain, new powers will
OL,12,Falso be introduced to restrict
OL,13,Fflavours which are specifically
OL,14,Fmarketed at children and ensure that
OL,15,Fmanufacturers produce plainer
OL,16,Fpackaging and change how vapes are
OL,17,Fdisplayed in shops, moving them out of
OL,18,Fchildren's sight.JNew #100 fines will
OL,19,Falso be brought in for shops in
OL,20,FEngland and Wales which sell vapes
OL,21,Fillegally to children.JTrading
OL,22,Fstandards officers will be given
OL,23,Fpowers to act "on the spot" to tackle
OL,24,Funderage tobacco and vape sales. This
OL,25,Fbuilds on a maximum #2,500 fine that
OL,26,Flocal authorities can already impose.
